[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6713,
        "end_time": 9754,
        "text": "&quot;All men are created equal"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9754,
        "end_time": 11708,
        "text": "and they are endowed with the rights to"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 11708,
        "end_time": 16110,
        "text": "life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness.&quot;"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 16110,
        "end_time": 18404,
        "text": "Not so fast, Mr. Jefferson!"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 18404,
        "end_time": 21454,
        "text": "These words from the Declaration of Independence,"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 21454,
        "end_time": 24002,
        "text": "and the facts behind them, are well known."
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 24002,
        "end_time": 26323,
        "text": "In June of 1776,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 26323,
        "end_time": 29890,
        "text": "a little more than a year after the war against England began"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 29890,
        "end_time": 32986,
        "text": "with the shots fired at Lexington and Concord,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 32986,
        "end_time": 36825,
        "text": "the Continental Congress was meeting in Philadelphia"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 36825,
        "end_time": 40048,
        "text": "to discuss American independence."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 40048,
        "end_time": 43499,
        "text": "After long debates, a resolution of independence"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 43499,
        "end_time": 47946,
        "text": "was approved on July 2, 1776."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 47946,
        "end_time": 49843,
        "text": "America was free!"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 49843,
        "end_time": 54599,
        "text": "And men like John Adams thought we would celebrate that date forever."
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 54599,
        "end_time": 57675,
        "text": "But it was two days later that the gentlemen in Congress"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 57675,
        "end_time": 61280,
        "text": "voted to adopt the Declaration of Independence,"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 61280,
        "end_time": 63858,
        "text": "largely written by Thomas Jefferson,"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 63858,
        "end_time": 68504,
        "text": "offering all the reasons why the country should be free."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 68504,
        "end_time": 71235,
        "text": "More than 235 years later,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 71235,
        "end_time": 75538,
        "text": "we celebrate that day as America&#39;s birthday."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 75538,
        "end_time": 79004,
        "text": "But there are some pieces of the story you may not know."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 79004,
        "end_time": 81567,
        "text": "First of all, Thomas Jefferson gets the credit"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 81567,
        "end_time": 83358,
        "text": "for writing the Declaration,"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 83358,
        "end_time": 85489,
        "text": "but five men had been given the job"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 85489,
        "end_time": 88811,
        "text": "to come up with a document explaining why"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 88811,
        "end_time": 91066,
        "text": "America should be independent:"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 91066,
        "end_time": 92352,
        "text": "Robert Livingston,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 92352,
        "end_time": 93737,
        "text": "Roger Sherman,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 93737,
        "end_time": 95190,
        "text": "Benjamin Franklin and"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 95190,
        "end_time": 97768,
        "text": "John Adams were all named first."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 97768,
        "end_time": 100594,
        "text": "And it was Adams who suggested that the young,"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 100594,
        "end_time": 103738,
        "text": "and little known, Thomas Jefferson join them"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 103738,
        "end_time": 108147,
        "text": "because they needed a man from the influential Virginia Delegation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 108147,
        "end_time": 113245,
        "text": "and Adams thought Jefferson was a much better writer than he was."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 113245,
        "end_time": 116470,
        "text": "Second, though Jefferson never used footnotes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 116470,
        "end_time": 118614,
        "text": "or credited his sources,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 118614,
        "end_time": 122025,
        "text": "some of his memorable words and phrases were borrowed"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 122025,
        "end_time": 125044,
        "text": "from other writers and slightly tweaked."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 125044,
        "end_time": 128922,
        "text": "Then, Franklin and Adams offered a few suggestions."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 128922,
        "end_time": 133725,
        "text": "But the most important change came after the Declaration"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 133725,
        "end_time": 136259,
        "text": "was turned over to the full Congress."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 136259,
        "end_time": 139835,
        "text": "For two days, a very unhappy Thomas Jefferson"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 139835,
        "end_time": 144183,
        "text": "sat and fumed while his words were picked over."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 144183,
        "end_time": 148930,
        "text": "In the end, the Congress made a few, minor word changes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 148930,
        "end_time": 151624,
        "text": "and one big deletion."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 151624,
        "end_time": 154346,
        "text": "In the long list of charges that Jefferson made"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 154346,
        "end_time": 156042,
        "text": "against the King of England,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 156042,
        "end_time": 158965,
        "text": "the author of the Declaration had included the idea"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 158965,
        "end_time": 163205,
        "text": "that George the Third was responsible for the slave trade,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 163205,
        "end_time": 167500,
        "text": "and was preventing America from ending slavery."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 167500,
        "end_time": 169611,
        "text": "That was not only untrue,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 169611,
        "end_time": 172602,
        "text": "but Congress wanted no mention of slavery"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 172602,
        "end_time": 175871,
        "text": "in the nation&#39;s founding document."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 175871,
        "end_time": 177194,
        "text": "The reference was cut out"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 177194,
        "end_time": 181382,
        "text": "before the Declaration was approved and sent to the printer."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 181382,
        "end_time": 183708,
        "text": "But it leaves open the hard question:"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 183708,
        "end_time": 185188,
        "text": "How could the men,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 185188,
        "end_time": 187294,
        "text": "who were about to sign a document,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 187294,
        "end_time": 190195,
        "text": "celebrating liberty and equality,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 190195,
        "end_time": 194374,
        "text": "accept a system in which some people owned others?"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 194374,
        "end_time": 196393,
        "text": "It is a question that"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 196393,
        "end_time": 199292,
        "text": "would eventually bring the nation to civil war"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 199292,
        "end_time": 202322,
        "text": "and one we can still ask today."
    }
]